Provenience: Napoli, Tomba del Tuffatore, p. 142, fig. 49; Hurschmann, op. cit., p. 149 and p. 198, no. P4.
Imagery Description: I. Symposium—to left standing draped woman (with incised inscription ΕΜΑΥTΑ), two banqueters on a couch. Exergue: reclining nude youth. Ext.: laurelNon Sepcifiedwreath, in added white, with central flower.
